.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-AGE" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-age \- show age of channels in days
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-age
.RI [ channel_id ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns each channel's open timestamp and computed age in days.
Without
.IR channel_id ,
returns all channels sorted oldest first.
Returns an empty array if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
[{channel_id, peer_id, state, opened_at, age_days}]
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-list (1),
.BR lightning-channel-balance (1)
